  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nOur current ECDSAContractAccount does not increment a nonce when a contract creation fails. This is because we do not catch contract creation reverts here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/cb2e9ad2548788613f2c135258ae8a7e5ba917be/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/accounts/OVM_ECDSAContractAccount.sol#L104-L113\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Create an EOA\r\n2. Deploy a contract which is expected to revert\r\n3. Check that nonce has not incremented after the contract wallet.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nNonce should increment even if the contract creation fails.\r\n\r\n",
